ese]], American colonel, lawyer, and politician, 75th [[United States Attorney General]] *[[1933]] &ndash; [[Peter Harding (RAF officer, born 1933)|Peter Robin Harding]], English marshal and pilot * 1933 &ndash; [[Mike Larrabee]], American sprinter and educator (d. 2003) *[[1934]] &ndash; [[Tarcisio Bertone]], Italian cardinal * 1934 &ndash; [[Andre Rodgers]], Bahamian baseball player (d. 2004) *[[1935]] &ndash; [[David Hackett Fischer]], American historian, author, and academic *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Manohar Joshi]], Indian lawyer and politician, 15th [[Chief Minister of Maharashtra]] *[[1939]] &ndash; [[Yael Dayan]], Israeli journalist, author, and politician * 1939 &ndash; [[Francis Fox]], Canadian lawyer and politician, 48th [[Secretary of State for Canada]] * 1939 &ndash; [[Harry Reid]], American lawyer and politician, 25th [[Lieutenant Governor of Nevada]] *[[1940]] &ndash; [[Willie Brown (American football)|Willie Brown]], American football player, coach, and manager *[[1941]] &ndash; [[Mike England]], Welsh footballer and manager * 1941 &ndash; [[Tom McGuinness (musician)|Tom McGuinness]], English guitarist, songwriter, author, and producer *[[1942]] &ndash; [[Anna G. Jónasdóttir]], Icelandic political scientist and academic *[[1943]] &ndash; [[Wayne Allard]], American veterinarian and politician *[[1944]] &ndash; [[Ibrahim Rugova]], Kosovan journalist and politician, 1st [[President of Kosovo]] (d. 2006) * 1944 &ndash; [[Dionysis Savvopoulos]], Greek singer-songwriter * 1944 &ndash; [[Botho Strauß]], German author and playwright *[[1945]] &ndash; [[Penelope Spheeris]], American director, producer, and screenwriter * 1945 &ndash; [[Alan Thomson (cricketer)|Alan Thomson]], Australian cricketer *[[1946]] &ndash; [[John Banks (New Zealand politician)|John Banks]], New Zealand businessman and politician, 38th [[Mayor of Auckland City]] * 1946 &ndash; [[Pedro Borbón]], Dominican-American baseball player (d. 2012) * 1946 &ndash; [[David Macaulay]], English-American a