{{Infobox comedian <!-- for groups - see Template:Infobox comedian for usage --> | name = Million Dollar Extreme | image = File:mde.jpg | image_size = 200px | alt = | caption = | pseudonym = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | medium = Web, television, stand-up, literature | nationality = United States | alma_mater = <!-- If the same for all members --> | active = | genre = Satire, [[sketch comedy]] | influences = <!--deprecated--> | influenced = <!--deprecated--> | notable_work = ''[[Million Dollar Extreme Presents: World Peace]]'' | memorials = | current_members = {{plain list| * [[Sam Hyde]] * {{not a typo|Charls}} Carroll * Nick Rochefort }} | past_members = | website = | footnotes = | module = }}
'''Million Dollar Extreme''' ('''MDE''') is an American [[sketch comedy]] troupe.<ref name=PhillyMag>{{cite web|last1=Thompson|first1=Andrew|title=WATCH: TEDx Drexel Got Pranked This Weekend|url=http://www.phillymag.com/news/2013/10/06/tedx-prank-philadelphia-drexel-sam-hyde/|publisher=[[Philly Mag]]|date=October 6, 2013}}</ref> They are known for their online videos, [[anti-comedy]], and public pranks.<ref name=AVClub2013 /> The members are [[Sam Hyde]], {{not a typo|Charls}} Carroll, and Nick Rochefort.<ref name=deadline />
==''World Peace''== {{Main|Million Dollar Extreme Presents: World Peace}}
On May 7, 2015, it was announced that MDE were slated to have their own live action 15-minute sketch show on the cable network [[Adult Swim]].<ref name=Stanhope2015>{{cite web|last1=Stanhope|first1=Kate|title=Adult Swim Upfront Slate Includes 12 Pilots, Two From 'Robot Chicken's' Seth Green|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/adult-swim-upfronts-slate-2015-793960|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> It was to be set in a post-apocalyptic nightmare world that satirizes the current political climate.<ref name="deadline">{{cite web|last1=Lincoln|first1=Ross|title=Adult Swim Comedy From Sketch Troupe Million Dollar Extreme Gets Series Order, Official Title|url=http://deadline.com/2016/03/sketch-troup-million-dollar-extreme-adult-swim-series-order-official-title-1201713596/|website=deadline.com|accessdate=March 5, 2016}}</ref> Titled ''[[Million Dollar Extreme Presents: World Peace]]'', the series premiered on August 5, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.adultswim.com/videos/million-dollar-extreme-presents-world-peace/|title=Million Dollar Extreme Presents: World Peace|publisher=|accessdate=December 11, 2016}}</ref> ''World Peace'' was subject to internal controversy at Adult Swim due to MDE's documented ties<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/josephbernstein/neo-nazi-promo-adult-swim-million-dollar-extreme#.pbwxy9Keb|title=The Underground Neo-Nazi Promo Campaign Behind Adult Swim’s Alt-Right Comedy Show|work=BuzzFeed News|access-date=2018-08-15|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.buzzfeednews.com/article/josephbernstein/adult-swim-talent-trying-to-cancel-million-dollar-extreme|title=Adult Swim Talent Want The Network To Cancel Its Alt-Right Comedy Show|work=BuzzFeed News|access-date=2018-08-15|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sam-hyde-speaks-meet-man-behind-adult-swims-canceled-alt-right-comedy-show-954487|title=Sam Hyde Speaks: Meet the Man Behind Adult Swim's Canceled "Alt-Right" Comedy Show (Exclusive)|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-08-15|language=en}}</ref> to the [[alt-right]]. Three weeks later, it was announced that the show would not be renewed for a second season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/tv/news/adult-swim-cancels-controversial-million-dollar-extreme-w454098|title=Adult Swim Cancels Controversial Show ‘Million Dollar Extreme’|last=Blistine|first=Joe|date=December 5, 2016|work=|publisher=Rolling Stone|via=}}</ref>
The troupe has run into various issues with online [[terms of service]] violations due to their content and fanbase. On May 4, 2018, the MDE channel was permanently removed from [[YouTube]] for a violation of the community guidelines.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/12/17847186/reddit-qanon-milliondollarextreme-ban-sam-hyde|title=Reddit has banned QAnon|last=Stephen|first=Bijan|date=12 September 2018|work=[[The Verge]]|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref> On September 10th, 2018, the group's subreddit on [[Reddit]] was permanently removed for violations of their policy regarding violent content.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://buzzfeednews.com/article/ishmaeldaro/reddit-sam-hyde-million-dollar-extreme-ban|title=Reddit Banned A Page That Trafficked In White Supremacist Content, But The Problem Is Much Bigger|last=Daro|first=Ishmael|date=11 September 2018|work=[[Buzzfeed News]]|accessdate=13 September 2018}}</ref>
==Critical reception== Christian Williams of ''[[The A.V. Club]]'' describes them: "Some videos borrow ''[[Wonder Showzen]]''{{'}}s toolkit, wielding subliminal blips and eye-straining text in service of subversive ends. Some make use of the ''[[Tim And Eric Awesome Show, Great Job!]]'' aesthetic, and some are surprisingly slick, with excellent, eardrum-shredding music courtesy of talented mystery-men like Orangy and Vaervaf."<ref name=AVClub2013>{{cite web|last1=Williams|first1=Christian|title=Take in the work of the comedy provocateurs in Million Dollar Extreme|url=http://www.avclub.com/article/take-in-the-work-of-the-comedy-provocateurs-in-mil-96712|website=[[The A.V. Club]]|date=April 23, 2013}}</ref> In the view of [[Philly Mag]]'s Andrew Thompson: "The mission of Million Dollar Extreme has always seemed a spin on afflicting the comfortable, except its targets usually aren’t the comfortably powerful. To the extent that satire exists in MDEs comedy, it feels like more of rationalization than a reason for the shock itself."<ref name=PhillyMag /> Robert Mariani wrote at ''[[The Federalist (website)|The Federalist]]'' that the group's comedy style is an example of [[post-irony]]: "Figuring out the intentions of the ironist is easy: whatever is being shown is being mocked. But the post-ironist folds over on his own sincerity with exaggeration, using the ironic not just to ridicule, but also to enjoy the absurdities of what he genuinely appreciates."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thefederalist.com/2016/12/12/million-dollar-extremes-adult-swim-show-becomes-collateral-damage-trumps-victory/|title=Million Dollar Extreme’s Show Is Collateral Damage Of Trump’s Victory|first=|last=Television|date=December 12, 2016|publisher=}}</ref>
