e van Daal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/list/ls033529958/|title=The ShortCutz Amsterdam Jury|last=|first=|publisher=imdb.com|date=January 26, 2016|accessdate=March 3, 2018}}</ref> |- | 2018 || [[Tygo Gernandt]] || [[Roel Reiné]], [[Rutger Hauer]], [[Vincent van Ommen]], [[Willeke van Ammelrooy]], [[Jan Harlan]], [[Sigrid ten Napel]], [[Eddy Terstall]], [[René Wolf]], [[Pieter Kuijpers]], [[Marina Blok]], [[Laser 3.14]], [[Claire van Daal]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/list/ls033529958/|title=The ShortCutz Amsterdam Jury|last=|first=|publisher=imdb.com|date=January 26, 2016|accessdate=March 3, 2018}}</ref> |- |}
==Career Achievement Award== The Career Achievement Award has been awarded since 2013. The winners are: 2017 - [[Heddy Honigmann]]<ref>[https://www.idfa.nl/nl/artikel/98356/heddy-honigmann-krijgt-shortcutz-amsterdam-career-award Heddy Honigmann krijgt Shortcutz Amsterdam Career Award] (January 18, 2017).</ref><ref>[https://www.hollandfilmnieuws.nl/nieuwscategorieen/beurzen-festivals/heddy-honigmann-geeerd-op-vijfde-shortcutz/ Heddy Honigmann geëerd op vijfde Shortcutz] (January 18, 2017).</ref>, 2016 - [[Pieter Kuijpers]]<ref>[https://www.filmfestival.nl/profs_nl/nieuws/nieuws-januari-2017/pieter-kuijpers-ontvangt-shortcutz-amsterdam-career-award/ Pieter Kuijpers ontvangt Shortcutz Amsterdam Career Award] (January 23, 2017).</ref>, 2015 - [[Rutger Hauer]]<ref>[http://www.parool.nl/kunst-en-media/oeuvreprijs-voor-acteur-rutger-hauer~a4228986/ Rutger Hauer receives Career Award] (January 20, 2016).</ref>, 2014 - [[Jos Stelling]]<ref>[http://hollandsefilm.nl/director-jos-stelling-receives-career-award-at-sold-out-shortcutz-amsterdam-annual-awards/ Director Jos Stelling receives Career Award] (January 8, 2015).</ref> and 2013 - [[George Sluizer]].
== Mr. Zee Award winners == The Mr. Zee Award has various sponsors, including [[ShortsTV]],<ref>[http://eu.shorts.tv/includes/article.php?article=31 ShortsTV and ShortCutz Amsterdam partner in Dutch short films] ''Shorts.tv,'' (January 16th, 2014)</ref> Camalot Amsterdam, Filmmore and [[EYE Film Institute Netherlands]]. The Mr. Zee awards are made by ProtoSpace.
